[~mmunn1]:

I was able to set up the instance churn using ELB and Autoscaling group.  However, I wasn't able to reproduce the metadata service to fail.  It looks like the version of Eucalyptus I used to create this bug last year (4.0.0) doesn't have the improvements that are available in 4.1.2. In the original use case, I could create the issue with only 2 instances in the AutoScaling group.  I tried with 5 instances, and there were no issues.  I will let the churn run for the rest of the night, and check in the morning to see if there are any issues.

Here are the steps I used to attempt to create the issue:

*Steps*

# Set up a 4.1.2 cloud in QA [Job hspencer-134 maint-4.1|http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint-4.1/134/] with Eucalyptus DNS enabled.
# Bundle, upload and registered Ubuntu Wily Cloud image
{code}
# euca-install-image -i wily-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.raw --arch x86_64 -b ubuntu-wily-amd64 -n ubuntu-wily-x86_64 --progress --virtualization-type hvm
{code}
# Created a security group
{code}
# euca-create-group nginx-sg -d "Security Group for Nginx Servers"
# euca-authorize -P tcp -p ssh nginx-sg
# euca-authorize -P tcp -p http nginx-sg
{code}
# Created a keypair
{code}
# euca-create-keypair nginx-webserver > nginx-webserver.pem
# chmod 0600 nginx-webserver.pem
{code}
# Created an Autoscaling Launch Config that uses cloud-init to install nginx
{code}
# euscale-create-launch-config NginxLaunchConfig --image-id emi-00ddffc9 --instance-type m1.small --group nginx-sg --key nginx-webserver --user-data-file nginx-cloudinit.config
{code}
# Create a load balancer
{code}
# eulb-create-lb NginxLoadBalancer --availability-zones cadillactica --listener "lb-port=80, protocol=HTTP, instance-port=80, instance-protocol=HTTP"
{code}
# Authorize load balancer to access nginx security group
{code}
# euca-authorize nginx-sg -u 867345899215 -o euca-internal-867345899215-NginxLoadBalancer -p -1
{code}
# Create autoscaling group
{code}
# euscale-create-auto-scaling-group NginxScalingGroup --launch-configuration NginxLaunchConfig --load-balancers NginxLoadBalancer --availability-zones cadillactica --min-size 5 --max-size 5
{code}
# Update health check type for autoscaling group
{code}
# euscale-update-auto-scaling-group NginxScalingGroup --health-check-type ELB --grace-period 30
{code}
# Configure healthcheck for ELB
{code}
# eulb-configure-healthcheck NginxLoadBalancer --target "HTTP:80/" --interval 30 --timeout 2 --unhealthy-threshold 2 --healthy-threshold 2
{code}

*Next Steps*

I suggest we get an environment in QA to where we can run 200 instances in the autoscaling group.  This way, we can get a similar use case that is used by the customer. 

Let me know if there are any questions.  Hope this helps.

*Update*

Checked on the cloud today (July 13, 2015).  Issue still didn't show up.  [~mmunn1]/[~sgraham], I will leave the cloud up in case you guys want to look at  it.  Let me know when you are done reviewing it so I can blow it away.
